    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>Levin's textbook builds counting from careful set-theoretic arguments. The Scheme implementations here use exact integer arithmetic, so no overflow or rounding issues for moderate inputs. The multiplicative formula for C(n,k) avoids computing full factorials. Python's math.comb (3.8+) does the same internally.</p>

